node.text:
Sunday strolls üåø 

My response to the Twitter comment claiming New Zealand is a hell hole because according to them most of the county is in lockdown, that we can't leave or go anywhere or see anyone, and that we have quarantine camps: 

Thankfully we live in a country that values the life of ALL their community members. Our response to the latest covid19 outbreak is to ensure the health and safety of the elderly and those who are vulnerable .

Level 3 lockdown for us Aucklanders are still local trips to the beach, reserves and walkways. We have our family bubbles and we still keep in contact with our neighbours. We practice social distancing and where needed wear masks. It is our temporary reality but it is one I am more than willing to wait out to ensure our community stays safe .

This is our fight. This is our response. This is Aotearoa .

node.text:
Who are you missing the most during this lockdown? It has been 6 weeks since @patrickhillstories left for Canberra, and @laurenleeinnisyouren is missing him more each day!

“Some days are harder than others, and I miss him so much... Knowing we can still make the music we love even with all the distance in between makes it a little better. I can’t wait to see his new recording set up - let’s hope the neighbours don’t mind a bit of crooning!” ~ Lauren Lee

With our Swellegant duo spilt between locations, we feel for those who have been separated from their partners, family, and loved ones during this second lockdown, and we want to share some love around! Do you have someone you are missing? Give them a shoutout in the comments and we’ll give them a shoutout in our next video!

Stay strong, everyone. Love from all of us at Swellegant üíö
